WEBVTT

00:01.083 --> 00:07.375
♪

00:07.375 --> 00:08.792
(laughing)

00:08.792 --> 00:11.667
TIM: No, it’s--
What are you talkin’--

00:11.667 --> 00:13.208
This is nice, isn’t it?

00:13.208 --> 00:14.542
You know, walkin’ home
from dinner.

00:14.542 --> 00:15.750
We should do this more often.

00:15.750 --> 00:17.375
Yeah!

00:17.375 --> 00:18.375
Or, we could drink less,

00:18.375 --> 00:20.166
-and then we could drive home.
-True.

00:20.166 --> 00:21.834
Hey, look at this!

00:21.834 --> 00:23.875
Tyler’s school!

00:23.875 --> 00:26.667
It’s a nice place to just sit
and do nothin’, huh?

00:26.667 --> 00:29.166
God knows that’s all
Tyler ever does, come on.

00:29.166 --> 00:30.458
(laughing)

00:30.458 --> 00:33.917
Hey, I’m pretty funny
when I’m buzzed.

00:33.917 --> 00:35.875
HEATHER: You are!

00:35.875 --> 00:37.125
And tired.

00:37.125 --> 00:38.959
We’ve only walked two blocks.

00:38.959 --> 00:41.500
Well...

00:41.500 --> 00:43.125
You know, when I
was in high school,

00:43.125 --> 00:45.709
we used to rearrange the letters
on these signs all the time.

00:45.709 --> 00:48.834
-It’s a classic prank.
-Oh, we did that too!

00:51.667 --> 00:53.166
♪

00:53.166 --> 00:55.000
-Yeah, yeah.
-Yeah.

00:55.000 --> 01:00.041
♪

01:00.041 --> 01:02.333
HEATHER: Hey, hey!

01:02.333 --> 01:03.834
Hey, buddy,
how was school today?

01:03.834 --> 01:06.542
Anything classic happen?

01:06.542 --> 01:09.583
No, but someone
messed with our marquee.

01:09.583 --> 01:11.208
They changed
"freshman elections"

01:11.208 --> 01:13.208
to "fleshman erections."

01:13.208 --> 01:14.625
(laughing)

01:14.625 --> 01:17.083
What’s so funny? The school
cancelled our senior trip.

01:17.083 --> 01:18.250
Wait, wait, wait, what?

01:18.250 --> 01:20.792
Yeah, they have a zero
tolerance policy on vandalism.

01:20.792 --> 01:22.667
-The cops are looking into it.
-Oh.

01:22.667 --> 01:23.959
For switchin’ around
a couple letters?

01:23.959 --> 01:25.792
What--What are
they arresting people

01:25.792 --> 01:28.083
for doing crossword puzzles
over there now, what?

01:28.083 --> 01:29.625
Because of the nature
of the message,

01:29.625 --> 01:31.500
they’re actually
considering it a sex crime.

01:31.500 --> 01:33.375
-Oh, huh.
-Wow!

01:33.375 --> 01:36.959
-Wow, that is--
-I mean, that, that is

01:36.959 --> 01:38.750
-right outta left field.
-Yeah.

01:38.750 --> 01:41.750
Well, until someone confesses,
the senior trip is off,

01:41.750 --> 01:45.208
and Clementine said
there was a chance we’d sl--

01:45.208 --> 01:46.542
ski together.

01:46.542 --> 01:48.083
I thought you were
going to Hoover Dam?

01:51.458 --> 01:54.166
Do you think they’ve
skied together before?

01:54.166 --> 01:55.417
I don’t know,
I bet she’s a great

01:55.417 --> 01:57.875
-skier though.
-Oh, God, please don’t say that.

01:57.875 --> 01:59.709
PRINCIPAL BUNDY:
You’re Tyler’s parents, right?

01:59.709 --> 02:00.542
How can I help you?

02:00.542 --> 02:02.917
Uh, well, we wanted
to come down here

02:02.917 --> 02:05.917
and talk to you about
the vandalized sign.

02:05.917 --> 02:09.041
Ah, yes, we’ve received
many complaints.

02:09.041 --> 02:10.667
And some compliments,
too, right?

02:10.667 --> 02:12.750
I mean, you have to admit
it was pretty classic.

02:12.750 --> 02:14.667
-I found it vulgar.
-And vulgar.

02:14.667 --> 02:16.166
And due to its
sophomoric nature,

02:16.166 --> 02:18.667
we’re certain it’s
a junior or senior.

02:18.667 --> 02:22.125
Okay, well, uh,
actually it was us.

02:22.125 --> 02:25.625
We did it,
and we are really sorry.

02:25.625 --> 02:27.709
We thought we should
come down here and confess

02:27.709 --> 02:30.291
so that the senior trip
can go ahead as planned.

02:30.291 --> 02:33.166
You’re saying that
you rearranged the sign?

02:33.166 --> 02:35.792
We were a little tipsy
comin’ home from dinner.

02:35.792 --> 02:38.959
No, he was tipsy,
I only had four.

02:38.959 --> 02:40.875
I see.

02:40.875 --> 02:43.000
Well, thank you for bringing
this to my attention.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.375
I mean, we also, we just
thought we wanted to come down

02:45.375 --> 02:47.083
and model good behavior.

02:47.083 --> 02:49.500
I mean, today,
we weren’t before,

02:49.500 --> 02:50.792
-but we--
-Okay, well I have other things

02:50.792 --> 02:52.542
to get to, so...

02:52.542 --> 02:54.041
Thank you for having us.

02:54.041 --> 02:57.500
♪

02:57.500 --> 02:59.542
They think I did it.

02:59.542 --> 03:00.458
-What?
-Yeah.

03:00.458 --> 03:03.166
Everyone can go on
the senior trip now but me.

03:03.166 --> 03:05.667
Principal Bundy said that
you two came in to confess,

03:05.667 --> 03:07.083
which means that I did it

03:07.083 --> 03:09.625
because no adult would
do something so stupid.

03:09.625 --> 03:11.041
-It wasn’t stupid!
-Hey!

03:11.041 --> 03:14.041
-It was classic.
-Thank you.

03:14.041 --> 03:15.417
Oh, my God.

03:15.417 --> 03:18.417
You did do it,
what were you guys thinking?

03:18.417 --> 03:19.834
-I don’t know.
-I don’t know?

03:19.834 --> 03:21.375
That’s really your answer?

03:21.375 --> 03:23.250
Are, are, are you mad at us?

03:23.250 --> 03:24.959
I’m not mad.

03:24.959 --> 03:27.792
-I’m just disappointed.
HEATHER: Oh.

03:27.792 --> 03:30.166
-Tyler, hey, come on!
-Hey, hey, hey!

03:30.166 --> 03:31.500
You know what, we will
go in there tomorrow

03:31.500 --> 03:33.041
and we will fix
this whole thing.

03:33.041 --> 03:34.959
TYLER: For once,
I’d like to come home,

03:34.959 --> 03:37.083
have a nice dinner
with my family,

03:37.083 --> 03:38.291
do some homework,

03:38.291 --> 03:39.458
and then go to sleep

03:39.458 --> 03:41.583
without all this drama.

03:41.583 --> 03:42.583
Okay?

03:44.792 --> 03:46.041
TIM: Totally
disappointed in you.

03:46.041 --> 03:47.166
HEATHER: You did it!
TIM: You’re the one

03:47.166 --> 03:48.458
he’s disappointed in.

03:48.458 --> 03:50.041
(indistinct arguing)

03:50.041 --> 03:51.125
HEATHER: ...told her
her sweater looked nice.

03:51.125 --> 03:53.166
We could have left
this whole thing behind.

03:53.166 --> 03:55.917
♪

03:55.917 --> 03:58.500
No, honey, look,
this photo of your dad

03:58.500 --> 03:59.917
mooning the sign,

03:59.917 --> 04:01.750
that proves that
you’re innocent.

04:01.750 --> 04:03.583
GIRL: There he is.
BOY: Tyler!

04:03.583 --> 04:05.250
Heard you were the one
who did the sign.

04:05.250 --> 04:06.542
No, no, I--

04:06.542 --> 04:07.834
BOY: That was hilarious.

04:07.834 --> 04:09.542
Thank you, finally.

04:09.542 --> 04:12.709
Are you here to make
more excuses for your son?

04:12.709 --> 04:14.375
BOY: Nice, man.

04:14.375 --> 04:17.750
TYLER: Classic, right?
BOY: So dope!

04:17.750 --> 04:18.750
No.

04:18.750 --> 04:20.375
No, no, no, no, uh,

04:20.375 --> 04:22.333
we are here to let him
know once and for all

04:22.333 --> 04:26.542
that we are very disappointed
with his inappropriate prank.

04:26.542 --> 04:28.291
(students speaking indistinctly)

04:28.291 --> 04:30.208
HEATHER: Yeah.
-Even though it was a classic.

04:30.208 --> 04:32.583
Uh-huh, that’s right.

04:32.583 --> 04:34.417
(school bell ringing)

04:34.417 --> 04:35.709
Who knew it was
such a big deal?

04:35.709 --> 04:36.875
I mean, when we were
in high school,

04:36.875 --> 04:39.250
pranks were just harmless fun.

04:39.250 --> 04:40.583
People are so sensitive now.

04:40.583 --> 04:42.583
I guess we’ll just
have to adapt.

04:45.375 --> 04:48.125
TIM: Aw man, it’s like
they’re begging us!

04:48.125 --> 04:49.041
No, no, no, no!

04:49.041 --> 04:50.917
We gotta walk away,
we gotta, we--

04:50.917 --> 04:53.166
-I don’t know that I can!
-Yeah, you can, you can.

04:53.166 --> 04:54.500
Walk away, walk away.

04:54.500 --> 04:58.291
♪

04:58.291 --> 04:59.250
(knocking)

04:59.250 --> 05:00.709
Come in.

05:00.709 --> 05:02.291
-Hi.
JEN: Hi, Jake.

05:02.291 --> 05:04.000
JAKE: Sorry to interrupt.

05:04.000 --> 05:05.417
Oh, what is that?

05:05.417 --> 05:07.792
That is dinner for your family.

05:07.792 --> 05:09.000
-What?
-I didn’t want to let

05:09.000 --> 05:10.583
any of my cooking lessons
go to waste.

05:10.583 --> 05:13.375
There’s a blowtorch inside so
you can really scorch the duck,

05:13.375 --> 05:14.625
but tableside.

05:14.625 --> 05:16.458
Well, you know I love
a scorched duck.

05:16.458 --> 05:18.583
JAKE: Now, please, go home
to that baby already!

05:18.583 --> 05:20.500
-Oh, her name’s Lark.
-I know.

05:20.500 --> 05:22.458
I’m actually writing
a lullaby for her birthday.

05:22.458 --> 05:23.417
Have a nice evening.

05:23.417 --> 05:26.041
I like what
you’re throwin’ down.

05:26.041 --> 05:27.583
All right, bye-bye.

05:27.583 --> 05:29.000
♪

05:29.000 --> 05:30.000
JEN: Hi, honey!

05:30.000 --> 05:32.166
You’re home early.

05:32.166 --> 05:34.667
And with dinner.

05:34.667 --> 05:37.000
Hi, beautiful!

05:37.000 --> 05:38.417
I got so much work done today.

05:38.417 --> 05:40.792
My to-do list is now
a to-done list.

05:40.792 --> 05:42.208
GREG: Ah!

05:42.208 --> 05:43.750
Well, that’s impressive.

05:43.750 --> 05:45.041
Well, I had help.

05:45.041 --> 05:46.834
Oh, is it chapped lips Amber?

05:46.834 --> 05:48.667
I thought she was
a horrible assistant?

05:48.667 --> 05:50.000
JEN: Oh, no, Amber, no.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.500
Yeah, she went
to rehab for something,

05:52.500 --> 05:55.041
sex, or meth,
or elaborate nail art.

05:55.041 --> 05:57.250
Anyway, she and her
whore nails are out,

05:57.250 --> 05:58.709
and things are
running real smooth.

05:58.709 --> 06:00.083
-Ah, great!
-Yeah.

06:00.083 --> 06:01.333
So, who’s the new girl?

06:01.333 --> 06:03.458
Hm, oh, uh, just um--

06:05.333 --> 06:07.709
-I wanna know about your day.
-Oh, well, psh.

06:07.709 --> 06:10.083
Ah, it’s always the same
at a crowd funding website.

06:10.083 --> 06:13.000
You know, just making
stupid dreams come true.

06:13.000 --> 06:15.041
Yeah, today someone got
50 grand to fund a hammer

06:15.041 --> 06:16.375
that says "nailed it."

06:16.375 --> 06:18.542
Yeah, oh, I invested in it.

06:18.542 --> 06:20.041
(doorbell dinging)

06:20.041 --> 06:21.166
Who’s that?

06:21.166 --> 06:22.417
I don’t know.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
-Oh, Jake.
JAKE: Sorry to bother you, Jen,

06:30.000 --> 06:33.458
but you left the Dufresne
brief in the office.

06:33.458 --> 06:35.834
-Um, oh, okay, I’ll take that.
JAKE: No, it’s heavy.

06:35.834 --> 06:37.583
I’ll just put it
right here on the table.

06:37.583 --> 06:39.875
No, no, no, no,
um, hey, you know,

06:39.875 --> 06:42.417
you didn’t have to run that
all the way over here.

06:42.417 --> 06:44.250
JAKE: Oh, it’s just a little
warm-up before my workout.

06:44.250 --> 06:45.917
-It’s no big deal.
-Ah.

06:45.917 --> 06:47.959
Hi, you must be Mr. Short.

06:47.959 --> 06:50.041
Oh, oh, have you never met?

06:50.041 --> 06:52.792
Uh, no, no, no, we haven’t.

06:52.792 --> 06:54.166
Jake, your wife’s secretary.

06:56.500 --> 06:57.959
Gregory.

06:57.959 --> 06:59.333
Greg for short.

06:59.333 --> 07:02.125
Uh, my wife’s husband.

07:02.125 --> 07:04.750
JEN: Well, we’ve had a lot of
laughs here tonight together,

07:04.750 --> 07:07.625
and I think, uh,
let’s just call it.

07:07.625 --> 07:09.250
So, okay.

07:09.250 --> 07:11.667
(utensils crashing)

07:14.250 --> 07:15.500
Dumb hammer!

07:15.500 --> 07:19.333
♪

07:19.333 --> 07:22.500
So, uh, Jake seems terrific!

07:22.500 --> 07:25.000
JEN: Really, you’re fine
with him being my assistant?

07:25.000 --> 07:26.875
-Uh-huh.
-Gosh, I thought for sure

07:26.875 --> 07:27.875
as soon as you saw him

07:27.875 --> 07:31.959
that pull-up bar would be
back in the door jamb.

07:31.959 --> 07:33.375
(plastic clambering)

07:33.375 --> 07:35.000
No, no, not at all.

07:35.000 --> 07:36.417
What was that,
did something just fall?

07:36.417 --> 07:38.458
Huh? What?

07:38.458 --> 07:39.542
Um...

07:39.542 --> 07:41.375
♪

07:41.375 --> 07:42.792
You smell like cookies.

07:42.792 --> 07:48.125
♪

07:48.125 --> 07:50.458
Jakey, man!

07:50.458 --> 07:52.333
-What’s happenin’?
JAKE: Mr. Short!

07:52.333 --> 07:54.166
-Hey, how are you?
GREG: Pound it.

07:54.166 --> 07:55.125
Oh, no.

07:55.125 --> 07:56.750
-Nice jacket.
-Oh, this old thing?

07:56.750 --> 08:00.583
Psh, I’ve had it for ages,
it’s one of Jen’s favorites.

08:00.583 --> 08:04.792
Oh, you’ve, you’ve
still got the tag on it.

08:04.792 --> 08:05.959
Phh.

08:07.667 --> 08:11.875
JEN: Uh, hi, hi honey.
-Oh, there’s my queen!

08:11.875 --> 08:13.250
Come here,
give me some sugar.

08:13.250 --> 08:14.375
What?

08:21.750 --> 08:23.500
Wow, that, that was...

08:23.500 --> 08:25.792
a week’s worth, so thanks.

08:25.792 --> 08:27.875
What exactly are you...

08:27.875 --> 08:29.709
-doing here?
-Well, I just happen to have

08:29.709 --> 08:31.625
a sixth sense when it comes
to what my woman needs,

08:31.625 --> 08:33.750
and I saw this,
and I thought I’d just

08:33.750 --> 08:34.959
run it on over.

08:34.959 --> 08:36.500
No big D.

08:36.500 --> 08:38.667
This is my Filofax from 2003.

08:38.667 --> 08:40.375
Anytime you see a red heart
in the calendar,

08:40.375 --> 08:41.500
it means that we banged.

08:41.500 --> 08:42.917
-Oh, my God.
-Okay?

08:42.917 --> 08:45.208
(phone ringing)

08:45.208 --> 08:46.750
Excuse me.

08:46.750 --> 08:49.041
Jen Collins-Short’s office.

08:49.041 --> 08:50.709
Oh, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

08:50.709 --> 08:53.166
Jakey boy,
what was that I heard?

08:53.166 --> 08:55.333
Squeak, yeah, your chair’s
a squeaker, all right?

08:55.333 --> 08:57.875
Nine out of ten times
it’s because of the hydraulics,

08:57.875 --> 09:00.166
so let me take a look
under the hood, come on.

09:00.166 --> 09:01.667
Let me see, just--

09:06.250 --> 09:07.458
Throw your back out again?

09:07.458 --> 09:09.709
-Yeah.
-Okay.

09:09.709 --> 09:11.291
Come here, baby.

09:11.291 --> 09:13.291
All right.

09:13.291 --> 09:14.333
♪

09:14.333 --> 09:16.709
It’s okay,
just give him a minute.

09:16.709 --> 09:18.125
(groaning)

09:18.125 --> 09:19.625
♪

09:19.625 --> 09:21.250
You okay?

09:21.250 --> 09:23.166
I’m fine.

09:23.166 --> 09:25.709
Did you thank Jake
for carrying me in here?

09:25.709 --> 09:28.417
Yeah, he just ran to his car
to grab his massage table.

09:28.417 --> 09:30.583
He’s also a certified
physical therapist.

09:30.583 --> 09:32.250
I’m just gonna assume
that he is everything

09:32.250 --> 09:33.542
until you tell me otherwise.

09:33.542 --> 09:36.500
Look, honey, you don’t have to
be threatened by him, okay?

09:36.500 --> 09:38.959
You’re my husband,
and I love you.

09:38.959 --> 09:41.000
But if this really upsets you,

09:41.000 --> 09:44.208
I will fire a perfectly
innocent, hard-working guy

09:44.208 --> 09:47.208
who helps your wife
be at the top of her game.

09:47.208 --> 09:48.834
Is tha--Is that what you want?

09:48.834 --> 09:50.667
Well...

09:50.667 --> 09:53.375
if you put it like that...

09:53.375 --> 09:55.917
Yeah, that’s exactly
what I want.

09:55.917 --> 09:57.375
Okay, well,
legally I can’t fire him,

09:57.375 --> 10:00.583
but I do appreciate you
finally being honest with me.

10:00.583 --> 10:01.709
JAKE: Okay, Mr. Short,

10:01.709 --> 10:04.375
I am not taking no
for an answer.

10:04.375 --> 10:06.750
It was my fault for letting
that chair get so squeaky.

10:06.750 --> 10:10.125
I should have fixed it
when I built that desk.

10:10.125 --> 10:12.458
-Wow, he really is good.
-Isn’t he?

10:12.458 --> 10:15.959
Wish I could find
an assistant like you.

10:15.959 --> 10:18.083
Actually,
my sister just graduated

10:18.083 --> 10:19.417
from Oxford University,

10:19.417 --> 10:20.959
and she would
love to work for you.

10:20.959 --> 10:23.125
If the Miss Universe circuit
taught her anything,

10:23.125 --> 10:25.917
it was the value of hard work.

10:25.917 --> 10:27.625
She sounds good!

10:27.625 --> 10:28.875
Yeah, okay, you’re fired.

10:28.875 --> 10:31.750
♪

10:31.750 --> 10:33.291
JOAN: Oh, it’s really in there.

10:33.291 --> 10:36.125
-Just stay calm.
-I am calm.

10:36.125 --> 10:37.333
No, I’m talking to myself.

10:40.250 --> 10:42.750
♪

10:42.750 --> 10:43.959
HEATHER: Hi, Mom.
JOAN: Hi, honey.

10:43.959 --> 10:45.583
Hey, you guys look,
Mom-Mom’s making dinner,

10:45.583 --> 10:48.083
so you eat whatever it is
that she makes you.

10:48.083 --> 10:49.792
Keep an eye on this one
because she has become

10:49.792 --> 10:52.500
very creative about
not eating her vegetables.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.166
Oh, I remember
all your old tricks.

10:54.166 --> 10:56.083
You used to stuff
your bra with broccoli.

10:56.083 --> 10:57.417
HEATHER: And this one over here

10:57.417 --> 10:59.125
just got her period,
so she’s not

10:59.125 --> 11:00.208
-a lot of fun right now.
-Mom!

11:00.208 --> 11:02.333
What, she gets it,
well, she used to.

11:02.333 --> 11:03.917
-She remembers.
JOAN: It’s okay, sweetie,

11:03.917 --> 11:06.291
-we’ll still have some fun.
HEATHER: Listen to Mom-Mom.

11:06.291 --> 11:07.834
JOAN: Have fun, dear.

11:07.834 --> 11:08.875
Bye, Mom.

11:08.875 --> 11:11.208
Shh, we gotta play it cool.

11:11.208 --> 11:13.959
You’re not safe until
that car leaves the driveway.

11:13.959 --> 11:14.917
♪

11:14.917 --> 11:16.041
(laughing)

11:16.041 --> 11:17.917
It’s always so fun over here.

11:17.917 --> 11:19.208
I wish we lived closer.

11:19.208 --> 11:21.583
We live across the street,
you stupid imp.

11:21.583 --> 11:25.208
I know you’re still in there,
my sweet Samantha.

11:25.208 --> 11:26.458
Come back to me.

11:26.458 --> 11:29.125
Let’s focus on...

11:29.125 --> 11:30.625
-bubbles!
-SOPHIA: Okay.

11:30.625 --> 11:33.834
One, two...

11:33.834 --> 11:35.000
Mm.

11:36.792 --> 11:37.750
Oh.

11:37.750 --> 11:38.875
(laughing)

11:38.875 --> 11:41.250
SOPHIA: Can I have another
piece, Mom-Mom, I lost mine.

11:41.250 --> 11:43.834
Oh, I think I found it.

11:43.834 --> 11:45.375
Oh, no!

11:45.375 --> 11:47.125
Oh, oh, oh, don’t move, honey,

11:47.125 --> 11:50.750
it’ll just go in worse.

11:50.750 --> 11:53.792
Okay, oh, it’s really in there.

11:53.792 --> 11:55.792
Just stay calm.

11:55.792 --> 11:58.000
-I am calm.
-No, I’m talking to myself.

11:58.000 --> 12:00.625
Honey, just--your mom
is gonna be so furious.

12:00.625 --> 12:04.375
She has no idea
what we do over here.

12:04.375 --> 12:05.709
Can I have another piece of gum?

12:05.709 --> 12:07.834
-No, no, no, no more gum.
-But it helps me

12:07.834 --> 12:09.000
when I’m stressed.

12:09.000 --> 12:11.125
Oh, of course you can, honey.

12:11.125 --> 12:12.792
Just let me get this piece out,

12:12.792 --> 12:14.333
and then you get another piece.

12:14.333 --> 12:16.083
Okay.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.125
Boop!

12:17.125 --> 12:18.667
♪

12:18.667 --> 12:20.166
This might be a stupid question,

12:20.166 --> 12:22.583
but can we chew the gum out?

12:22.583 --> 12:25.417
No, honey, I think we’re gonna

12:25.417 --> 12:27.291
try the peanut butter next.

12:27.291 --> 12:28.417
I ate it all.

12:28.417 --> 12:29.917
Damn it!

12:29.917 --> 12:31.417
Oh, I’m so sorry, honey.

12:31.417 --> 12:33.250
I wasn’t, I wasn’t
cursing at you.

12:33.250 --> 12:36.333
I was cursing with you.

12:36.333 --> 12:38.041
I can curse?

12:38.041 --> 12:39.291
No.

12:39.291 --> 12:41.417
-Well, maybe a couple.
TYLER: Hey, Mom-Mom,

12:41.417 --> 12:43.709
I got the Vaseline you wanted?

12:43.709 --> 12:45.458
Thanks, honey.

12:45.458 --> 12:48.458
Oh, this has the look
of Mom blowing up.

12:48.458 --> 12:49.625
I’m out.

12:49.625 --> 12:50.667
SAM: Me too.

12:50.667 --> 12:52.125
Good luck, people.

12:52.125 --> 12:53.542
Hey, hey, guys!

12:53.542 --> 12:55.500
Who bought you
thong panties last week

12:55.500 --> 12:57.166
when your mom wouldn’t?

12:57.166 --> 12:59.959
And Tyler, who’s got your back
when you tell you mom

12:59.959 --> 13:02.208
you’re sleeping over here,
and you don’t?

13:02.208 --> 13:04.166
You know, horses of a feather,

13:04.166 --> 13:06.625
they don’t abandon the ship.

13:06.625 --> 13:07.917
(scissors snipping)

13:07.917 --> 13:10.417
-Oh!
-Problem solved!

13:10.417 --> 13:11.583
JOAN: Oh, no!

13:11.583 --> 13:12.875
You’re welcome.

13:12.875 --> 13:13.917
Ugh.

13:13.917 --> 13:15.875
HEATHER: Look at
all this junk food!

13:15.875 --> 13:18.625
Mom, where’d this come from?

13:18.625 --> 13:19.709
I mean, when we were kids,

13:19.709 --> 13:22.625
the most sugary thing you would
let us have was cough syrup!

13:22.625 --> 13:24.500
Things change, honey.

13:24.500 --> 13:26.417
It’s the natural flow of life.

13:26.417 --> 13:28.667
Stop talking about my period!

13:28.667 --> 13:31.667
I just, I don’t understand it,
you were always so strict!

13:31.667 --> 13:32.792
Yeah, I was too strict,

13:32.792 --> 13:35.750
and it was a constant,
exhausting battle.

13:35.750 --> 13:37.709
And I had to sit there
and listen to you tell me

13:37.709 --> 13:40.083
how much more fun it was
over at Gi-Gi’s.

13:40.083 --> 13:41.625
Yeah, because Gi-Gi
would let me eat

13:41.625 --> 13:44.083
an entire tube of cookie dough!

13:44.083 --> 13:46.208
Don’t look at me.

13:46.208 --> 13:49.166
-Oh.
-Honey, I was always saying no.

13:49.166 --> 13:51.792
-Now it’s my time to say yes.
-Okay, I just,

13:51.792 --> 13:52.959
I don’t know
how comfortable I am

13:52.959 --> 13:54.500
having the kids over here
if I know you don’t

13:54.500 --> 13:56.291
-respect my rules.
SOPHIA: But, Mom,

13:56.291 --> 13:58.709
you let Pop-Pop smoke cigars
in our backyard,

13:58.709 --> 14:00.458
even though
he’s not supposed to.

14:00.458 --> 14:02.000
-Shh!
-Oh, boy.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.000
You do what?

14:03.000 --> 14:04.709
It’s not my job to tell him no.

14:04.709 --> 14:06.250
-John!
-Well, Tyler’s smokin’

14:06.250 --> 14:08.625
a lot more than cigars
out in my shed.

14:08.625 --> 14:10.250
Why don’t you ride his ass?

14:10.250 --> 14:11.834
-Pop-Pop?
JOHN: I just came in here

14:11.834 --> 14:13.500
for some cookie dough.

14:13.500 --> 14:15.291
-Damn it, Samantha.
-Damn it to you.

14:15.291 --> 14:18.125
JOAN: Oh, now, now,
we’re all very frustrated,

14:18.125 --> 14:21.291
but at least there’s
no more secrets between us!

14:21.291 --> 14:22.875
TIM: Hey, John,
the neighbors are

14:22.875 --> 14:26.250
shooting porn
in their yard again.

14:26.250 --> 14:28.583
TIM: Ah, damn.
HEATHER: Hm!

14:28.583 --> 14:30.875
I found your binoculars.

14:30.875 --> 14:34.834
♪

14:34.834 --> 14:36.166
JOHN: Tank is not ridiculous!

14:36.166 --> 14:37.375
(yipping)

14:37.375 --> 14:39.917
She is the mayor
of doggie pack city.

14:43.125 --> 14:46.333
♪

14:46.333 --> 14:47.917
JOHN: It’s great to see ya.

14:47.917 --> 14:49.458
Been missing you
around the house.

14:49.458 --> 14:50.959
Aw!

14:50.959 --> 14:53.291
You specifically,
or other people?

14:53.291 --> 14:56.625
I don’t know,
I’m just bein’ nice.

14:56.625 --> 14:59.041
Well, I think Princess
really misses Matt.

14:59.041 --> 15:01.083
JOHN: What does it mean when
they sniff around like that?

15:01.083 --> 15:02.792
COLLEEN: Sometimes when
a dog’s head goes one way,

15:02.792 --> 15:05.208
its butt goes the other,
doesn’t mean anything.

15:05.208 --> 15:08.000
Wow, you know
so much about dogs!

15:08.000 --> 15:09.750
-Lots!
-Cool.

15:11.250 --> 15:13.083
You know,
we should do this again.

15:13.083 --> 15:14.583
It’s nice to catch up...

15:14.583 --> 15:16.041
about dogs and parks,

15:16.041 --> 15:19.291
-and Matt.
-Sure.

15:19.291 --> 15:21.250
But maybe don’t mention
that we’re hanging out

15:21.250 --> 15:23.792
in case he’s feeling raw
about the breakup.

15:23.792 --> 15:26.625
Sneaking around,
that sounds fun.

15:26.625 --> 15:29.250
Uh, what do you call an affair

15:29.250 --> 15:32.583
when there’s no sex
with the other person?

15:32.583 --> 15:33.667
A friendship.

15:33.667 --> 15:39.834
♪

15:43.083 --> 15:44.750
Hey, Dad, where you been?

15:44.750 --> 15:48.417
Uh, at the store because
we’re outta cheese.

15:48.417 --> 15:49.834
I mean bread,
did I say cheese?

15:49.834 --> 15:52.083
I don’t know why
I would say cheese.

15:52.083 --> 15:55.917
-Um, I was at the post office.
-Uh, did you get stamps?

15:55.917 --> 15:59.000
Why would I get stamps
at the dog park?

15:59.000 --> 16:01.458
-Hm?
-Oh, damn it, uh, geez!

16:01.458 --> 16:03.250
I’m sorry you had to
find out this way.

16:03.250 --> 16:05.166
I had to find out tha--What?

16:05.166 --> 16:06.959
I just told you
I was with Colleen!

16:06.959 --> 16:08.250
No, you didn’t
just tell me that.

16:08.250 --> 16:10.083
Oh, well, then forget
I said anything.

16:10.083 --> 16:11.125
MATT: Hey, whoa, whoa!

16:11.125 --> 16:12.458
Hm?

16:12.458 --> 16:13.875
You were with Colleen?

16:13.875 --> 16:16.709
Yeah, she’s
helpin’ me with Tank.

16:16.709 --> 16:19.083
-Okay.
-What, you’re not mad at me?

16:19.083 --> 16:20.125
No, of course not.

16:20.125 --> 16:21.500
You’re an adult
with a ridiculous dog,

16:21.500 --> 16:22.875
she’s an adult
with a ridiculous dog.

16:22.875 --> 16:24.291
I just don’t need
to hear about it.

16:24.291 --> 16:25.625
JOHN: Tank is not ridiculous!

16:25.625 --> 16:26.875
(yipping)

16:26.875 --> 16:29.166
She is the mayor
of doggie pack city.

16:29.166 --> 16:30.834
♪

16:30.834 --> 16:33.417
(yipping)

16:33.417 --> 16:34.333
JOHN: Huh?

16:34.333 --> 16:36.875
Wow, look at Tank and Princess!

16:36.875 --> 16:38.750
You had professional
portraits made?

16:38.750 --> 16:40.291
Yeah, imagine
the wedding night, huh?

16:40.291 --> 16:41.291
(laughing)

16:41.291 --> 16:42.750
-No thanks.
-You owe me 23 bucks,

16:42.750 --> 16:44.834
but you can pay me anytime.

16:44.834 --> 16:47.917
♪

16:47.917 --> 16:50.333
(iPad ringing)

16:56.625 --> 16:58.083
John, hi.

16:58.083 --> 16:59.500
-Hey!
-Hi, it’s really late.

16:59.500 --> 17:00.542
Is everything okay?

17:00.542 --> 17:02.083
Yeah, oh, no, I know it’s late,

17:02.083 --> 17:04.208
but there’s someone here
that can’t wait ’till morning

17:04.208 --> 17:05.375
-to talk to you.
-Oh!

17:07.750 --> 17:11.000
<i>Hi, I got a new collar!</i>

17:11.000 --> 17:12.083
<i>You like it?</i>

17:12.083 --> 17:13.250
It’s really cute.

17:13.250 --> 17:14.417
I’m going to bed.

17:14.417 --> 17:15.667
(whining)

17:15.667 --> 17:17.625
♪

17:17.625 --> 17:19.125
Oh, what’s this?

17:19.125 --> 17:21.917
I entered Princess and Tank
in a big dog show.

17:21.917 --> 17:23.500
First prize is a Geo Storm,

17:23.500 --> 17:25.250
so we should
drive there together

17:25.250 --> 17:26.750
in case one of us wins.

17:26.750 --> 17:28.750
John, I don’t think
I can do this.

17:28.750 --> 17:31.208
No, no, I know
Princess is a mutt,

17:31.208 --> 17:33.583
but I lied to them about
the pedigree, so it’s fine.

17:33.583 --> 17:38.041
No, no, I’ve been meaning
to talk to you about this.

17:38.041 --> 17:39.417
I love the time
that we spend together.

17:39.417 --> 17:42.000
-Hmm.
-But it’s too much.

17:42.000 --> 17:44.166
-Hm?
-And it’s too complicated.

17:47.000 --> 17:50.166
I think we should
start seeing other dogs.

17:50.166 --> 17:51.375
Oh.

17:51.375 --> 17:52.917
-I see.
-Yeah.

17:54.792 --> 17:56.333
Here, Tank, here!

17:56.333 --> 17:57.709
(barking)

18:00.250 --> 18:01.792
John, I’m sorry.

18:01.792 --> 18:02.875
By the way,

18:02.875 --> 18:04.500
this whole time Tank has been

18:04.500 --> 18:07.000
sharing the water bowl
at Boston Market

18:07.000 --> 18:09.000
with a really good lookin’ pug.

18:09.000 --> 18:11.917
♪

18:11.917 --> 18:14.417
(video game sound effects)

18:14.417 --> 18:15.959
♪

18:15.959 --> 18:17.834
I think Tank misses Princess.

18:17.834 --> 18:20.458
Dad, we agreed that we
are not gonna discuss Colleen.

18:20.458 --> 18:22.959
No, this is not about Colleen.

18:22.959 --> 18:24.792
I was just thinking
that maybe you had some

18:24.792 --> 18:27.417
visitation rights
with Princess that you could

18:27.417 --> 18:28.834
-take advantage of.
-Damn it, Dad,

18:28.834 --> 18:31.208
I’m trying really hard
to move on from her.

18:31.208 --> 18:33.250
Don’t do it for me, son.

18:33.250 --> 18:35.625
Do it for
your little sister here.

18:35.625 --> 18:39.333
<i>Help me, don’t punish me</i>
<i>for things our father did!</i>

18:39.333 --> 18:40.917
Okay, first of all, don’t refer
to her as my little sister,

18:40.917 --> 18:42.375
and second of all,
don’t use that voice!

18:42.375 --> 18:44.750
Do it, or get
outta my house, huh?

18:44.750 --> 18:46.250
You already used
that this morning

18:46.250 --> 18:48.041
when you told me
to kill the spider.

18:48.041 --> 18:50.500
There’s no limit to
how many times I can use it.

18:50.500 --> 18:53.417
♪

18:53.417 --> 18:54.583
Oh, God.

18:58.083 --> 19:01.208
Good job!
Get the ball, good going!

19:01.208 --> 19:03.125
MATT: So excited,
so excited, I know.

19:03.125 --> 19:06.750
♪

19:06.750 --> 19:08.417
Hey.

19:08.417 --> 19:11.625
-Hi.
-Hi.

19:11.625 --> 19:12.792
COLLEEN: How are--
-How are, how are you?

19:12.792 --> 19:13.959
(laughing)

19:13.959 --> 19:15.417
Good, how are you?

19:15.417 --> 19:18.125
I’m good, um...

19:18.125 --> 19:19.917
I hear my dad
got a little needy.

19:19.917 --> 19:21.000
You heard right.

19:21.000 --> 19:22.333
Don’t know how you
didn’t see that comin’.

19:22.333 --> 19:24.166
(laughing)

19:24.166 --> 19:25.583
Um...

19:25.583 --> 19:27.083
I should call up Greg,
get him down here.

19:27.083 --> 19:29.250
You can break up with
all the men in my family.

19:29.250 --> 19:32.333
-Well then, okay.
-Oh, come on, jokes!

19:35.041 --> 19:36.959
You look good.

19:36.959 --> 19:38.083
-You too!
-Change your hair?

19:38.083 --> 19:39.500
Nope.

19:39.500 --> 19:40.750
-Have you lost weight?
-No.

19:40.750 --> 19:42.166
Did something
with your eyebrows?

19:42.166 --> 19:43.166
-Sure.
-Knew it.

19:43.166 --> 19:44.125
-Mm-hm.
-Mm-hm.

19:44.125 --> 19:46.000
-Very perceptive.
-Thank you.

19:48.458 --> 19:49.959
So, I know that Tank
needs a friend,

19:49.959 --> 19:51.625
and so, um, since my dad
is too much for you,

19:51.625 --> 19:53.542
maybe I could...

19:53.542 --> 19:56.417
bring her by once in a while.

19:57.625 --> 19:58.542
I’d like that.

20:01.000 --> 20:02.792
-All right.
-Okay.

20:07.375 --> 20:08.625
All right,
you wanna say goodbye?

20:08.625 --> 20:10.291
-Bye, Tank, see ya soon.
-All right, say goodbye.

20:10.291 --> 20:11.709
See you very soon.

20:11.709 --> 20:14.583
-Very soon, yeah.
-Yeah.

20:14.583 --> 20:17.208
Very soon sounds good,
okay, all right.

20:17.208 --> 20:18.542
-Okay.
-Okay.

20:20.208 --> 20:22.667
♪

20:22.667 --> 20:23.792
Hi!

20:23.792 --> 20:30.709
♪

20:39.000 --> 20:40.000
How’s Princess?

20:40.000 --> 20:41.250
He’s, he’s good.

20:41.250 --> 20:42.667
And how are you?

20:42.667 --> 20:43.625
I’m okay.

20:43.625 --> 20:45.834
It’s nice how fate
brought you two together.

20:45.834 --> 20:47.750
-Yeah.
-Well, let’s get outta here,

20:47.750 --> 20:49.458
and go get a cheeseburger.

20:49.458 --> 20:51.125
Fate is gettin’ hungry.

20:51.125 --> 20:58.041
♪

21:16.291 --> 21:19.041
♪
